===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|phonetics}} A sound produced by the [[vocal cords]] with relatively little restriction of the [[oral cavity]], forming the prominent sound of a [[syllable]].
#: {{ux|en|In Welsh, the ''w'' usually represents a '''vowel'''.}}
# {{lb|en|orthography}} A [[letter]] representing the sound of vowel; in English, the vowels are ''a'', ''e'', ''i'', ''o'', ''u'', and ''y''.
#: {{ux|en|''{{1|facetious}}'' is spelled with five '''vowels''' in alphabetical order.}}

